<br>
That same night my group had an exp leach (caster casting one spell on our pulls to syphon exp). We asked him to stop many times and finally we all /appealed. It's been about a week and that's still in line. A friend did get a reply and it seems that this guy is going to find himself picking a new name as he gets transfered to a non-roleplay server. His name was the same as one of the dungeons in Albion.<br>
<br>
Second.. You lose 1 con point for the first death of each level, 2 for the second death and 3 from every death in that level from then on. If you get a res you recieve less experiance back (assuming you pray if you don't get a res) but you do not lose the con points. I'm still not really sure what Res effects does though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uarakazul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arakazul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/24/01 8:54:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hehe</span><hr size=1> Ok a couple points. <br>
